  "text": "# Grafana Three-Tier Permission Model Implementation\n\nGrafana implements a comprehensive three-tier permission model (Viewer/Editor/Admin) across the following key components:\n\n## 1. Role Type Definitions\n\nThe fundamental role types are defined in **pkg/apimachinery/identity/role_type.go** (RoleType, RoleViewer, RoleEditor, RoleAdmin) with a precedence system where Admin > Editor > Viewer > None. The RoleType includes:\n- `Includes()` method to check role hierarchy\n- `Children()` and `Parents()` methods for role relationships  \n- `rolePrecedence` map defining precedence values (10-40)\n\nThese are aliased in **pkg/services/org/model.go** for organizational context.\n\n## 2. Role-to-Permission Mapping\n\nThe core role-to-permission mapping is established in **pkg/services/accesscontrol/roles.go**:\n\n- **BuildBasicRoleDefinitions()**: Creates the three basic roles (Admin, Editor, Viewer) with UIDs like \"basic_admin\", \"basic_editor\", \"basic_viewer\"\n- **DeclareFixedRoles()**: Registers roles and their permission grants\n- Uses prefixes: \"basic:\" for basic roles, \"fixed:\" for fixed roles, \"managed:\" for managed roles\n\nResource-specific action mappings are defined in:\n\n**pkg/services/accesscontrol/ossaccesscontrol/dashboard.go**:\n- `DashboardViewActions`: READ permissions\n- `DashboardEditActions`: READ + WRITE + DELETE permissions  \n- `DashboardAdminActions`: READ + WRITE + DELETE + PERMISSIONS READ/WRITE\n- `registerDashboardRoles()`: Declares dashboard roles for each tier\n\n**pkg/services/accesscontrol/ossaccesscontrol/folder.go**:\n- `FolderViewActions`: READ, ALERTING_READ, LIBRARY_READ, SILENCES_READ\n- `FolderEditActions`: VIEW + WRITE + DELETE + CREATE dashboards + alerting rules\n- `FolderAdminActions`: EDIT + PERMISSIONS READ/WRITE\n- `registerFolderRoles()`: Declares folder roles for each tier\n\n## 3. Permission Guard Middleware\n\nPermission enforcement is implemented through middleware layers:\n\n**pkg/services/accesscontrol/middleware.go**:\n- `Middleware()`: Core permission checking middleware that evaluates actions against user permissions\n- `authorize()`: Executes evaluator and denies access if evaluation fails\n- `AuthorizeInOrgMiddleware()`: Validates user has permissions in target organization\n- Uses scope injection and mutation for dynamic scopes\n\n**pkg/middleware/middleware.go**:\n- `ReqEditorRole`: Middleware for Editor+Admin role requirement\n- `ReqOrgAdmin`: Middleware for Admin-only requirement\n- Basic role authentication middleware definitions\n\n**pkg/middleware/auth.go**:\n- `RoleAuth()`: Simple middleware checking if user's OrgRole matches required roles\n- Uses `c.OrgRole` to check against allowed roles\n- `Auth()`: Authentication options middleware\n- `SnapshotPublicModeOrCreate()`, `SnapshotPublicModeOrDelete()`: Conditional permission checks\n\n## 4. Permission Evaluation System\n\n**pkg/services/accesscontrol/evaluator.go**:\n- `Evaluator` interface: Defines permission evaluation contract\n- `EvalPermission()`: Creates evaluator checking specific action+scopes\n- `EvalAll()`: Creates evaluator requiring all sub-evaluators pass\n- `permissionEvaluator.Evaluate()`: Checks if user permissions match required action/scopes\n- Implements wildcard matching for scope patterns (e.g., \"folders:*\")\n\n**pkg/services/accesscontrol/acimpl/accesscontrol.go**:\n- `Evaluate()`: Core access control evaluation method\n- Evaluates permissions after resolving scopes\n- Handles scope resolution via ScopeAttributeResolvers\n\n## 5. Folder/Dashboard Permission Inheritance\n\nPermission inheritance through folder hierarchy:\n\n**pkg/services/dashboards/accesscontrol.go**:\n- `GetInheritedScopes()`: Retrieves parent folder scopes for a resource\n  - Calls `folderSvc.GetParents()` to traverse ancestor folders\n  - Returns scopes for all ancestor folders in the hierarchy\n  - Returns nil for General folder (no inheritance)\n- `NewFolderUIDScopeResolver()`: Scope resolver that includes folder + all ancestor scopes\n- `NewDashboardUIDScopeResolver()`: Dashboard resolver that includes folder hierarchy\n- `resolveDashboardScope()`: Returns dashboard + folder + ancestor scopes for evaluation\n\n**pkg/services/folder/folderimpl/folder.go**:\n- `GetParents()` query: Retrieves ancestor folders for a given folder UID\n- Folder permissions are inherited from parent folders\n- Comments in code: \"if the parent is accessible then the subfolders are accessible as well (due to inheritance)\"\n\n**pkg/services/folder/folderimpl/folder_unifiedstorage.go**:\n- `getAvailableNonRootFolders()`: Filters folders based on user's folder and dashboard permissions\n- Combines parent folder permissions with dashboard permissions\n- Handles permission hierarchy: EDIT permissions include READ permissions\n\n## 6. Authorization Model\n\n**pkg/services/accesscontrol/authorizer.go**:\n- `ResourceResolver`: Interface for translating resources to scopes\n- `LegacyAccessClient`: Maps K8s verbs to RBAC actions\n- Default mapping: Get→read, Create→create, Update→write, Delete→delete, SetPermissions→permissions:write\n\n**pkg/api/accesscontrol.go**:\n- `declareFixedRoles()`: Declares all fixed roles for API operations\n- Registers roles with their grants to basic org roles\n- Defines permissions for provisioning, datasources, and other API operations\n\n## 7. Scope Model\n\nScopes provide fine-grained resource access:\n- Format: \"resource:uid:value\" (e.g., \"dashboards:uid:my-dashboard\", \"folders:uid:my-folder\")\n- Wildcards: \"folders:*\" matches all folders\n- Providers: ScopeFoldersProvider, ScopeDashboardsProvider for scope generation\n- Scope hierarchy respects folder/dashboard relationships\n\n## Summary\n\nThe three-tier permission model flows as:\n\n1. **Type Definition**: RoleType enum (pkg/apimachinery/identity/role_type.go)\n2. **Role Creation**: BuildBasicRoleDefinitions() in roles.go creates Admin/Editor/Viewer\n3. **Action Mapping**: registerDashboardRoles/registerFolderRoles map actions to roles\n4. **Middleware Enforcement**: RoleAuth/Middleware in middleware packages check org role\n5. **Permission Evaluation**: EvalPermission/Evaluate checks actions+scopes against user permissions\n6. **Inheritance**: GetInheritedScopes includes parent folder scopes in evaluation\n7. **Authorization**: AccessControl.Evaluate executes the full permission check with scope resolution"
}

